Spain remains Britons ' favourite destination to fly to , as it has been for more than 25 years .
New figures from the UK Civil Aviation Authority shows 238m passengers passed through British airports in 2014 , just three million less than the pre-recession boom of 241m in 2007 .
Germany proved a more visited destination than France and the US ahead of Spain and the Netherlands .
The United Arab Emirates ranks in the top 10 countries with a 13.2 m increase .